CHANGES0003 - Fixed cubical path splitting issue in c₁-vanish and c₁-alternating

Major changes:
1. FIXED c₁-vanish (path type splitting error):
   - Cubical Agda cannot bind path-typed variables (eq : σ fzero ≡ σ fone)
     on the LHS of function clauses that also do pattern matching on data types
   - Solution: use `λ eq →` on the RHS instead of binding `eq` on the LHS
   - Uses Tri<-elim (dependent eliminator) to case-split on Tri< without
     having path variables in the pattern matching context

2. REFACTORED c₁-alternating vanishing part:
   - Extracted c₁-alt-vanish helper that case-splits on Fin 2 indices
   - All clauses return a FUNCTION (λ eq → ...) rather than binding eq on LHS
   - For (i=fzero, j=fone): delegates to c₁-vanish
   - For (i=fone, j=fzero): delegates to c₁-vanish ∘ sym
   - Same-index cases: contradiction via Σ≡Prop
   - Absurd cases: ⊥.rec on proof component

3. Fixed unsolved metas: explicit {n = k} {m = 2} for isProp<ᵗ in Σ≡Prop calls

Remaining holes: snd(c₁-alternating) [antisymmetry], d-preserves-alt, section-exact
Remaining postulates: d², cπ-homotopic-to-id, contractible-with-section

